<item>
            <title>[BEAM-7561] HdfsFileSystem is unable to match a directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-7561</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://beam.apache.org/releases/javadoc/2.3.0/org/apache/beam/sdk/io/FileSystems.html#match-java.util.List-&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;FileSystems.match&lt;/a&gt; method should be able to match a directory according to javadoc. Unlike &lt;em&gt;HdfsFileSystems&lt;/em&gt;, &lt;em&gt;LocalFileSystems&lt;/em&gt; behaves as I would so I&apos;m assuming this is a bug on &lt;em&gt;HdfsFileSystems&lt;/em&gt; side.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Current behavior:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;em&gt;HadoopFileSystem.match(&quot;hdfs:///tmp/dir&quot;)&lt;/em&gt; returns a &lt;em&gt;MatchResult&lt;/em&gt; with an empty metadata&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected behavior:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;em&gt;HadoopFileSystem.match(&quot;hdfs:///tmp/dir&quot;)&lt;/em&gt; returns a &lt;em&gt;MatchResult&lt;/em&gt; with metadata about the directory&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;**&lt;/p&gt;</description>
